  "prompt": "What's a good video editor for windows?",
  "response": "There are several good video editors available for Windows, each catering to different needs and skill levels. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Adobe Premiere Pro**: A professional-grade video editing software with a wide range of features and tools. It's widely used in the industry and offers advanced editing capabilities.\n\n2. **DaVinci Resolve**: Known for its powerful color correction tools, DaVinci Resolve is also a robust video editor suitable for both professional and amateur video editors.\n\n3. **Final Cut Pro**: Although traditionally associated with macOS, some users run Final Cut Pro on Windows using virtualization or dual-boot setups. However, this is not a native Windows solution.\n\n4. **Sony Vegas Pro**: A professional video editing software with a user-friendly interface and a variety of advanced features.\n\n5. **HitFilm Express**: A free video editor that also offers VFX capabilities. It's great for beginners and intermediate editors.\n\n6. **Filmora**: An intuitive video editing software that's great for beginners. It offers a range of features and an easy-to-use interface.\n\n7. **Shotcut**: A free, open-source video editor that's quite powerful and suitable for both beginners and more experienced editors.\n\n8. **VSDC Free Video Editor**: Another free option that offers a range of features, including video effects, audio effects, and more.\n\n9. **Movavi Video Editor**: A user-friendly video editor that offers a good balance of features and ease of use.\n\n10. **Lightworks**: A professional-grade video editor with a free version that includes many powerful tools. The paid version offers additional features.\n\nEach of these editors has its strengths, so the best choice depends on your specific needs, budget, and level of expertise.",
